HEADWORD: Impanate
<hw>Im*pa"nate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>impanatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>impanare</ets> to impanate; L. pref.
<ets>im-</ets> in + <ets>panis</ets> bread.]</ety> <def>Embodied in
bread, esp. in the bread of the eucharist.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Cranmer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

